title: Develop (#53)
message:
Develop (#53)

* Permission requests (#47)

* Handle the deprecated of DigitalClock

* Remove unused imports

* Highlights the default room that was set in the settings (#42)

* Layouts for 7-inch tablets.

* Using non-resource calendars (#44)

* Extends API to use non-resource calendars for happy non-Google-Apps users.

* Changes preferences retrieval and setting to a centralised preference manager

* Enables walkthrough when user opens app for the first time. User can select account, whether he syncs non-resource calendars, visible rooms, default room.

* Implements error handling when going through wizard. User will be redirect to the settings page if errors happen during the process.

* Adds new options to settings page, reloads proxy after Google Account would have been changed

* Fixes an issue that the TrafficLight would close automatically after 45 seconds

* Show setup wizard if all account removed when the user is already in Lobby

* Hot fixed cannot compile

* Feature/check permission (#51)

* Adds Activity to check permissions and gitignore

* Configs xml files and gradle properties

* Changes code indentation to 4 tabs

* Only request permissions on API > 23

* Ignore .idea files

* Change description of the resources for the reservator (#52)

* Change description of the resources for the reservator

* Update README.md

title: Using non-resource calendars (#44)
message:

* Extends API to use non-resource calendars for happy non-Google-Apps users.

* Changes preferences retrieval and setting to a centralised preference manager

* Enables walkthrough when user opens app for the first time. User can select account, whether he syncs non-resource calendars, visible rooms, default room.

* Implements error handling when going through wizard. User will be redirect to the settings page if errors happen during the process.

* Adds new options to settings page, reloads proxy after Google Account would have been changed

* Fixes an issue that the TrafficLight would close automatically after 45 seconds

* Show setup wizard if all account removed when the user is already in Lobby

title: Import app to Android Studio using importer
message:
Import app to Android Studio using importer

ECLIPSE ANDROID PROJECT IMPORT SUMMARY
======================================

Ignored Files:
--------------
The following files were *not* copied into the new Gradle project; you
should evaluate whether these are still needed in your project and if
so manually move them:

* Reservator.apk
* ReservatorRelease-3.6.apk
* lib/
* lib/simple-xml-2.5.3.jar

Moved Files:
------------
Android Gradle projects use a different directory structure than ADT
Eclipse projects. Here's how the projects were restructured:

* AndroidManifest.xml => app/src/main/AndroidManifest.xml
* assets/ => app/src/main/assets/
* res/ => app/src/main/res/
* src/ => app/src/main/java/
* Test/res/ => app/src/androidTest/res/

Next Steps:
-----------
You can now build the project. The Gradle project needs network
connectivity to download dependencies.

Bugs:
-----
If for some reason your project does not build, and you determine that
it is due to a bug or limitation of the Eclipse to Gradle importer,
please file a bug at http://b.android.com with category
Component-Tools.

(This import summary is for your information only, and can be deleted
after import once you are satisfied with the results.)
